\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Men.\">Men.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">653</biblScope> </bibl>; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οὐδέποτε</foreign> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">tam in praeterito quam in futuro, quomodo et nos 'nunquam'</tr_>, <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Priscian.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Inst.\">Inst.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18.257</biblScope> </bibl>: in late writers the reference of <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">πω</itype> to past time was neglected, <xr opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"xr\"> <lbl opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"lbl\">v.</lbl> <ref targOrder=\"U\" lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"ref\">οὐδεπώποτε</ref></xr>, and cf. <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">ἐξ ὧν ἀνάγκη . . μηδεπώποτε ἐλευθερίας ἐπιτυγχάνειν</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0612.tlg001:14:1\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.Chr.\">D.Chr.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">14.1</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>; cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οὐδέπω, οὔποτε, οὔπω, οὐπώποτε</foreign>, also <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">μηδέποτε, μηπώποτε</foreign>.—In <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Hom.</author> </bibl> <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">οὐδέ ποτε</foreign> shd. prob. be written divisim: sts. a word is put between, as in <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:6:99\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">6.99</biblScope></bibl>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}